  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nOther (please describe)\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6130af7 2022-04-07T00:08:44.543037+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThis could be an issue with my specific machine (10.14 Mac), but on installation the PATH was lost after I closed the installation terminal session.  The installation script added the PATH to .bashrc, but I couldn't get the PATH to persist until I added it to .bash-profile. Now everything works as expected.",
